meanings.sent1: She managed to outjuggle all her friends at the juggling contest.
meanings.sent2: The circus performer could outjuggle anyone with her amazing skills.
meanings.sent3: Despite his efforts, he couldn't outjuggle the professional juggler at the fair.
meanings.sent4: Her ability to outjuggle others was like watching a master at work.
meanings.sent5: The young boy practiced every day to outjuggle his own record.

meanings.definition: To outdo in a competition of juggling abilities.
meanings.sent1: He was determined to outjuggle his rival in the juggling championship.
meanings.sent2: The siblings always tried to outjuggle each other for fun.
meanings.sent3: In a friendly match, she managed to outjuggle her brother with ease.
meanings.sent4: The magician could outjuggle any challenger who dared to compete.
meanings.sent5: The goal was to outjuggle the previous champion and claim the title.
